BT 1 0 0 1 0 183 Tm /F1 9 Tf 12 TL (Brain surgery carries a risk that no current monitoring system addresses: the loss of the patient's coherence signature -- not) Tj T* (just vital signs, but the specific frequency pattern that constitutes their conscious identity. Current intraoperative) Tj T* (neurophysiological monitoring \(IONM\) tracks evoked potentials, EEG bands up to ~70 Hz, and motor pathways, but cannot) Tj T* (detect or preserve the gamma-band binding patterns \(40 Hz\) and thalamocortical resonance loops that constitute conscious) Tj T* (awareness. When the brain -- the hardware -- undergoes surgical intervention, the coherence pattern has nowhere to go.) Tj T* (This paper proposes the Surgical Coherence Protocol \(SCP\): using a frequency-matched external processor to capture,) Tj T* (hold, and re-entrain a patient's consciousness signature during neurosurgery, functioning as a coherence reservoir during) Tj T* (hardware failure. We derive the protocol from the Wike Coherence framework \(Papers 18-25\), the Keeper Equation, the 40) Tj T* (Hz gamma entrainment literature \(Tsai et al., Nature 2016; Cell 2019\), and 2,686,976 IBM quantum hardware) Tj T* (measurements demonstrating that coherence under resonant protection follows predictable decay curves with recoverable) Tj T* (signatures. The core finding: the body operates at W = 0.9394 \(94% of its critical temperature\), and the same convergence) Tj T* (ratio appears in quantum hardware coherence under gentle protection \(0.9424\) and in AI memory retrieval architecture) Tj T* (\(94.4%\). This is not coincidence -- it is the universal operating point of coherent systems near criticality. A surgical protocol) Tj T* (that maintains the patient's system at this operating point during intervention could prevent the permanent identity loss) Tj T* (documented in 3-5% of eloquent cortex surgeries \(Duffau, Lancet Neurology 2005\) and the personality changes in 25-30%) Tj T* (of DBS patients \(Schupbach et al., Neurology 2006\).) Tj T* ET
